&lt;h3 data-start=&quot;240&quot; data-end=&quot;255&quot;&gt;About ESS&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;256&quot; data-end=&quot;589&quot;&gt;Effective School Solutions (ESS) is a leading provider of school-based mental health services for K–12 students, serving over 2,000 students across nine states. ESS delivers high-acuity clinical care within public schools, helping students with significant emotional and behavioral needs achieve academic and mental health stability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 data-start=&quot;596&quot; data-end=&quot;622&quot;&gt;About the Internship&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;623&quot; data-end=&quot;784&quot;&gt;ESS is seeking a &lt;strong data-start=&quot;640&quot; data-end=&quot;674&quot;&gt;graduate-level Clinical Counseling Intern&lt;/strong&gt; (Master’s in Clinical Counseling) for a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;742&quot; data-end=&quot;781&quot;&gt;full academic year unpaid placement&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;786&quot; data-end=&quot;1034&quot;&gt;This internship offers hands-on experience providing school-based mental health services under the supervision of a licensed clinician. Interns will be embedded within one school site and will work as part of a collaborative interdisciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
